lessons.append({
    "id": 721,
    "kanji": "\u8a31\u3059",
    "kana": "\u3086\u308b\u3059",
    "meaning": "to forgive, permit, allow",
    "tags": ["godan verb", "\u4ed6\u52d5\u8a5e"],
    "lesson": "<p>The kanji <span class=\"jp\">\u8a31</span> combines <span class=\"jp\">\u8a00</span> <span class=\"gloss\">(speech)</span> and <span class=\"jp\">\u5348</span> <span class=\"gloss\">(a pestle, originally a vertical pillar)</span>. The original sense was to give someone verbal passage \u2014 to speak words that remove a barrier. That double meaning lives on in modern Japanese: <span class=\"jp\">\u8a31\u3059</span> means both \"to forgive\" and \"to permit,\" and the connection between them is surprisingly deep. When you forgive someone, you\u2019re removing the barrier their transgression created. When you permit something, you\u2019re removing the barrier that was preventing it. Same action, different context.</p><p><span class=\"jp-example\">\u5f7c\u3092\u8a31\u3059</span> <span class=\"gloss\">(forgive him)</span>. <span class=\"jp-example\">\u5165\u5ba4\u3092\u8a31\u3059</span> <span class=\"gloss\">(permit entry)</span>. <span class=\"jp-example\">\u4f53\u304c\u8a31\u3055\u306a\u3044</span> <span class=\"gloss\">(my body won't allow it \u2014 I physically can't)</span>. That last usage is interesting: the subject isn't a person granting permission but a condition that does or doesn't tolerate something.</p><p><span class=\"note-label\">Sound anchor:</span> <span class=\"reading\">yu-ru-su</span> shares its first two syllables with <span class=\"jp\">\u7de9\u3044</span> <span class=\"gloss\">(\u3086\u308b\u3044, loose/slack)</span>. Both words carry a sense of loosening, releasing tension. To forgive is to loosen your grip on a grudge. To permit is to loosen a restriction. The sound family isn't etymological, but it's a useful memory hook.</p><p class=\"particle-note\"><span class=\"note-label\">Particles:</span> <span class=\"jp\">\u8a31\u3059</span> takes <span class=\"jp highlight\">\u3092</span> for the thing or person you forgive/permit. <span class=\"jp-example\">\u5f7c\u306e\u5931\u6557\u3092\u8a31\u3059</span> <span class=\"gloss\">(forgive his failure)</span>. When permitting an action, the action itself is the direct object: <span class=\"jp-example\">\u5916\u51fa\u3092\u8a31\u3059</span> <span class=\"gloss\">(permit going out)</span>.</p><p class=\"particle-note\"><span class=\"note-label\">Potential</span> <span class=\"jp-example\">\u304c\u8a31\u305b\u308b</span>: the thing that can be forgiven becomes the subject with <span class=\"jp highlight\">\u304c</span>. <span class=\"jp-example\">\u305d\u308c\u3060\u3051\u306f\u8a31\u305b\u306a\u3044</span> <span class=\"gloss\">(that alone I cannot forgive)</span>.</p><p class=\"particle-note\"><span class=\"note-label\">Passive</span> <span class=\"jp-example\">\u306b\u8a31\u3055\u308c\u308b</span>: <span class=\"jp highlight\">\u306b</span> marks who does the forgiving. <span class=\"jp-example\">\u5148\u751f\u306b\u8a31\u3055\u308c\u305f</span> <span class=\"gloss\">(I was forgiven by the teacher)</span>.</p><p class=\"particle-note\"><span class=\"note-label\">Causative</span> <span class=\"jp-example\">\u306b\u2026\u3092\u8a31\u3055\u305b\u308b</span>: <span class=\"jp highlight\">\u306b</span> marks the person you make forgive, <span class=\"jp highlight\">\u3092</span> marks what they forgive. Rare in practice \u2014 you can't easily force forgiveness.</p><div class=\"verb-meta\"><span class=\"group-badge\">\u4e94\u6bb5 Godan</span><span class=\"trans-badge\">\u4ed6\u52d5\u8a5e</span></div><table class=\"conj-chart\"><tr><td>Dictionary</td><td><span class=\"stem\">\u3086\u308b</span><span class=\"ending\">\u3059</span></td><td class=\"particle\">\u3092</td></tr><tr><td>Negative</td><td><span class=\"stem\">\u3086\u308b</span><span class=\"ending\">\u3055\u306a\u3044</span></td><td class=\"particle\">\u3092</td></tr><tr><td>Polite</td><td><span class=\"stem\">\u3086\u308b</span><span class=\"ending\">\u3057\u307e\u3059</span></td><td class=\"particle\">\u3092</td></tr><tr><td>Polite neg</td><td><span class=\"stem\">\u3086\u308b</span><span class=\"ending\">\u3057\u307e\u305b\u3093</span></td><td class=\"particle\">\u3092</td></tr><tr><td>Past</td><td><span class=\"stem\">\u3086\u308b</span><span class=\"ending\">\u3057\u305f</span></td><td class=\"particle\">\u3092</td></tr><tr><td>Polite past</td><td><span class=\"stem\">\u3086\u308b</span><span class=\"ending\">\u3057\u307e\u3057\u305f</span></td><td class=\"particle\">\u3092</td></tr><tr><td>\u3066-form</td><td><span class=\"stem\">\u3086\u308b</span><span class=\"ending\">\u3057\u3066</span></td><td class=\"particle\">\u3092</td></tr><tr><td>Volitional</td><td><span class=\"stem\">\u3086\u308b</span><span class=\"ending\">\u305d\u3046</span></td><td class=\"particle\">\u3092</td></tr><tr><td>Polite vol</td><td><span class=\"stem\">\u3086\u308b</span><span class=\"ending\">\u3057\u307e\u3057\u3087\u3046</span></td><td class=\"particle\">\u3092</td></tr><tr><td>Passive</td><td><span class=\"stem\">\u3086\u308b</span><span class=\"ending\">\u3055\u308c\u308b</span></td><td class=\"particle\">\u306b</td></tr><tr><td>Causative</td><td><span class=\"stem\">\u3086\u308b</span><span class=\"ending\">\u3055\u305b\u308b</span></td><td class=\"particle\">\u306b\uff0f\u3092</td></tr><tr><td>Caus-pass</td><td><span class=\"stem\">\u3086\u308b</span><span class=\"ending\">\u3055\u305b\u3089\u308c\u308b</span></td><td class=\"particle\">\u306b</td></tr><tr><td>Potential</td><td><span class=\"stem\">\u3086\u308b</span><span class=\"ending\">\u305b\u308b</span></td><td class=\"particle\">\u304c</td></tr><tr><td>Imperative</td><td><span class=\"stem\">\u3086\u308b</span><span class=\"ending\">\u305b</span></td><td class=\"particle\">\u3092</td></tr><tr><td>Imp \u306a\u3055\u3044</td><td><span class=\"stem\">\u3086\u308b</span><span class=\"ending\">\u3057\u306a\u3055\u3044</span></td><td class=\"particle\">\u3092</td></tr><tr><td>Cond \uff5e\u3070</td><td><span class=\"stem\">\u3086\u308b</span><span class=\"ending\">\u305b\u3070</span></td><td class=\"particle\">\u3092</td></tr><tr><td>Cond \uff5e\u305f\u3089</td><td><span class=\"stem\">\u3086\u308b</span><span class=\"ending\">\u3057\u305f\u3089</span></td><td class=\"particle\">\u3092</td></tr></table>"
})

